From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dfattal <dfattal@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 22:34:59 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 49/51] inline-3d(#28): exempt viewport-fixed exclusion rects
 from the impl-scroll patch

The sticky gallery header briefly blew up (~2x) over the woven tiles on a fast
scroll. Root cause was not Blink: a CDP rAF probe showed
#app-header.getBoundingClientRect() stable at y=0 h=56.8 CSS across 283 samples
with flings up to 40000 px/s. The drift was injected downstream, in cc.

LayerTreeHostImpl::MakeCompositorFrameMetadata's "#625 Phase 2 scroll-sync"
block shifts every reported rect by the viewport's impl-accumulated scroll
delta, to correct for scrolling that happened after the commit that supplied
the rects. That is right for content that scrolls with the viewport -- its own
comment says "the dominant case" -- and pure error for a viewport-fixed
element, which does not move with the scroll at all. Measured shifts ran to
+/-4700 device px, so on a fling the header rect either missed its quad
entirely or, when it went negative, got clipped at the surface top into a short
hole. Either way the exclusion no longer matched a root resource quad, so
display.cc never added it to SetInline3dSuppressedResources, so the header
stayed in the tile's SBS weave input and got woven. At rest the delta is zero
and on a slow scroll it stays inside best_match's 70% bar, which is why this
only ever showed up on a fast scroll.

Split the exclusion list: Blink puts rects whose element is viewport-fixed into
exclusion_fixed_rects, cc patches only the scrolling lists, then appends the
fixed list verbatim. Downstream (aggregator, GPU stage) still sees one flat
list and needs no change -- the split exists only to decide who gets the shift.
A position:sticky element is treated as fixed only while actually stuck
(non-zero StickyPositionOffset), since before it reaches its threshold it does
scroll with the content and the patch is correct for it.

Measured on the gallery, Official build, identical 8-fling workload:
  NO match for target      3652 -> 272 (the residual is mostly empty 0x0 rects)
  #22 (B) unmatched          27 -> 0
  header rects drifted    20/26 -> none logged
  overlays= steady state     12 -> 12 (canvas_res=6 both) -- none dropped
Weave healthy throughout (one submit, eyes_valid=1). Hardware-confirmed by
David: the pop is gone.

An earlier attempt moved exclusions onto the tracked-element channel
(draw-time ScreenSpaceTransform, like the canvas rects). It fixed the drift but
its per-frame fallback dropped overlays and let occasional bad frames through,
so it was reverted in favour of this.

The TreesInViz-in-client path is covered (it feeds UpdateDisplayTree from
metadata, after the append). The in-viz-process path does not carry the split
over its mojom update and keeps today's behaviour -- nothing dropped; noted in
a comment as a follow-up.

Refs: browser#28
